1-5 Hierarchical Clustering¶

  1. The similarity between clusters in a hierachical cluster graph is based on the (Y-AXIS/height | X-AXIS/width), which represents the distance between cluster groups for a given # of clusters. Clusters that merge at higher values are (MORE | LESS) similar than clusters that merge at lower values.
  1. The CSV file named 'automobiles.csv' is read into the Pandas Dataframe df for you below. The variables of df have been standardized and transformed according to their z-score, are stored into the numpy array Xdf.

Using scipy's hierarchy module, apply COMPLETE hierarchical clustering to Xdf and store the result into the variable hclust. Plot a dendrogram showing the complete linkage of hclust.

How many clusters is recommended (shown by the unique colors)?

df = pd.read_csv("automobiles.csv")
df_features = df.select_dtypes("number").copy()

Xdf = StandardScaler().fit_transform(df_features)

# SOLUTION
hclust = hierarchy.complete( Xdf )

In [ ]:

  1. Matching

  2. COMPLETE defines the distance between two clusters according to...

  3. SINGLE defines the distance between two clusters according to...

  4. AVERAGE defines the distance between two clusters according to...

  5. CENTROID defines the distance between two clusters according to...

  6. WARD defines the distance two between clusters according to...

  • the maximum distance between observations (furthest pair)
  • the minimum distance between observations (closest pair)
  • the distance between each cluster's centroid
  • the minimum within-cluster variance
  • the average distance between all observations within a cluster

6-8 PCA¶

  1. Which of the following is true about using PCA?
  • It reduces the dimensionality (# of variables) of a dataset
  • It is used to simplify and summarize the important features of a dataset
  • Principal components are generated in such a way that pc1 has the MOST variability and subsequent pcs have decreasing variability
  • PCA can only be applied to numerical features
  • PCA combines correlated variables into shared principle components
  1. The CSV file named 'automobiles.csv' is read into the Pandas Dataframe df for you below.

Using SEABORN, plot a heatmap showing the correlation matrix between all numeric variables in df. You must set the arguments vmin=-1 and vmax=1 within heatmap.

According to the correlation matrix:

  • Horsepower has a ___ correlation with city_mpg and highway_mpg
  • Stroke has a ___ correlation with peak_rpm
  • Curb weight has a ___ correlation with price

Strong positive, Weak, Strong negative

  • A city_mpg and highway_mpg are likely to be combined into a principal component relating to the overall "efficiency" of the vehicle
  • stroke, bore, peak_rpm and compression ratio are likely to be combined into a principal component relating to the "engine" type
